column2: Question
All in all, do you think things in the nation are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
In reference to Georgia specifically, do you think things in the state are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
As you think about the next 12 months, do you expect the strength of the U.S. economy to be better or worse as compared to the way you see it now?
What is the single most important issue facing Georgia today?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Joe Biden is handling his job as president?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Brian Kemp is handling his job as governor?
Do you approve or disapprove of the House of Representatives impeachment inquiry into President Joe Biden?
Should Georgia expand eligibility for Medicaid, which provides health care for some poor Georgians, to cover all the state’s uninsured poor?

Georgia’s abortion law bans most abortions after a fetal heartbeat is detected, as early as 6 weeks of pregnancy. Would you like to see the General Assembly make abortion harder to obtain, easier to obtain or would you like the current restrictions to remain?

Since 2019 the state has been using a new voting system than uses touchscreens to print out paper ballots. Do you support or oppose replacing this system with paper ballots that would be filled out by hand?
How confident are you that the 2024 presidential election will be conducted fairly and accurately?
Do you believe there was widespread voter fraud in the 2020 presidential election, or not?
Which comes closer to your line of thinking: supporting Israel is in the national interest of the United States or supporting Israel is not in the national interest of the United States?

The state constitution allows Georgia residents to attempt to change local laws by petitioning to get an issue on the ballot for citizens to vote on. Some officials say this creates the opportunity for groups to reverse governing decisions large and small; others say that citizens should have the opportunity to challenge government decisions if they can meet the high bar for getting them on the ballot. Do you approve or disapprove of this provision?

The Georgia Legislature is considering legislation that would allow the use of taxpayer funds to pay for private schooling in some circumstances. Do you support or oppose the use of taxpayer money to support students who want a private education?
How much you trust the schools in your district to ensure books in school libraries are appropriate for students?
How much you trust the schools in your district to teach about racism in the United States?
How much you trust the schools in your district to respond appropriately when a student poses a risk of doing something violent?
How much confidence do you have in the Georgia Legislature?
How much confidence do you have in Georgia K-12 public schools?
How much confidence do you have in Georgia’s colleges and universities?
How much confidence do you have in Georgia’s election system?
How much confidence do you have in Georgia law enforcement?
If the election were held today and the candidates for president were Democrat Joe Biden and Republican Donald Trump, for whom would you vote?
